Company/Sector Update



Infosys | Soft 4QFY26; Healthy large deal wins<https://jmflresearch.com/Dow=
nload?ReportId=3D21219&DownloadType=3Dshow>

Result Update              BUY                 INR 1,500

Infosys reported 4QFY26 results =96 revenue and margins were below expectat=
ions. Revenue declined 1.3% cc QoQ vs expectation of 0.5% cc QoQ decline. E=
BIT margins at 20.9% =96 missed JMFL and consensus expectations. Forward lo=
oking indicators =96 i) Infosys guided for 1.5%-3.5% YoY cc revenue growth =
for FY27 (includes 20-25bps of acquisition), lower than our expectation of =
2% to 4%, margin guidance was in-line at 20-22%. ii) LTM large deal TCV gre=
w ~28% YoY in FY26 versus decline of ~34% in FY25 (LTM book to bill of 0.74=
x in FY26 versus 0.60x in FY25). ii) Headcount declined 2.6% QoQ / up 1.6% =
YoY. iii) Management commentary =96 Lower end of guidance factors demand de=
terioration while top end factors demand improvement. Margin headwinds for =
FY27 also includes a potential 70bps dilutive impact from acquisitions. Pre=
fer Infosys among the top 6 Indian IT companies given healthy large deal wi=
ns. Valuations are at ~16x FY27 consensus EPS. We revise our EPS estimates =
down by 1-2% over FY27-28E, incorporating 4Q results. Maintain target multi=
ple of 19x Sep 27 =96 revised TP of INR 1,500 (versus INR 1525 earlier). Ma=
intain BUY.



Tata Capital | Strong growth and asset quality trends; miss on NIM<https://=
jmflresearch.com/Download?ReportId=3D21220&DownloadType=3Dshow>

Result Update              ADD                 INR 380

Tata Capital reported a healthy quarter with PAT growth at +47% YoY/+16% Qo=
Q (despite missing JMFe by 4.7%), and ~17bps/49bps increase in RoA/RoE at 2=
.1%/13%. This was driven by healthy AUM growth, improving asset quality and=
 continued operating leverage. AUM grew +20% YoY / +6% QoQ (28% YoY ex-TMFL=
), in-line with their guidance, led by sustained traction in retail, corpor=
ate and housing finance. TCHFL remained a standout with +29% YoY AUM growth=
 and best-in-class asset quality. However, at the overall level, NIM perfor=
mance remained relatively softer than expected (-9bps QoQ, -15bps JMFe) as =
asset-side repricing and higher corporate mix continued to weigh on yields,=
 leading to a miss in our PAT estimates. Credit cost improved sharply to 0.=
9% (0.8% ex-motor finance), while GS3/NS3 declined by 20bps/15bps QoQ. Moto=
r finance also showed improving profitability. Management remains confident=
 of delivering FY28 guidance of ~2.5=962.7% RoA (% of net loans) and >30% P=
AT CAGR. We believe improving earnings quality and motor finance normalisat=
ion support premium valuations. We build in EPS CAGR of ~34% during FY26-28=
E with average RoA (% of avg. assets)/RoE of ~2.2%/15% in FY27/28E (BAF/CIF=
C- EPS CAGR: ~28%/26%, RoA: ~4%/2.6%; RoE: ~21%/20% during the same period)=
. We maintain ADD with revised TP of INR380, valuing it at ~2.7/18x FY28 BV=
PS/EPS (vs. ~3.8/19x for BAF/ ~3.1/18x for CIFC).



LTM | Soft 4QFY26; valuation remains elevated<https://jmflresearch.com/Down=
load?ReportId=3D21218&DownloadType=3Dshow>

Result Update              REDUCE                       INR 4,115

LTM reported 4QFY26 results =96 revenues and margins were below versus expe=
ctations. Revenue growth came in at 1.2% cc QoQ versus expectation of 1.6% =
cc QoQ. EBIT margins at 15.1% versus JMFL/consensus expectations of 15.6%/1=
5.5%. Forward looking indicators =96 i) LTM order inflow grew 10.2% YoY in =
FY26 versus 7% YoY growth in FY25 (LTM book to bill of 1.4x in FY26 versus =
1.3x in FY25). ii) Headcount remained stable on a sequential basis (+4.3% Y=
oY). iii) Management commentary =96 confident to continue the growth moment=
um in FY27. However, due to certain macroeconomic environment that might ha=
ppen within the three months period, there could be some softness in a part=
icular quarter. Valuations are at ~21x FY27 consensus EPS. LTM is at ~7% pr=
emium to Mphasis for a similar growth profile in FY27, as per consensus. We=
 reduce our EPS estimates by 3-5% over FY27-28E, incorporating 4Q results. =
Maintain target multiple of 19x Sep 27 =96 revised TP of INR 4,115 (versus =
INR 4,285 earlier). Maintain REDUCE.



UTI AMC | Reports loss due to other income; all is well<https://jmflresearc=
h.com/Download?ReportId=3D21217&DownloadType=3Dshow>

Result Update              ADD                 INR 1,100

UTI AMC reported a loss of INR 514mn in 4Q only due to MTM losses resulting=
 in negative other income of INR 1,630mn. Operating performance was sound; =
revenue fell just 1% QoQ while QAAUM was down 3%. Employee expenses were ba=
ck to the trend rate of INR 1.3bn while other expenses were elevated with m=
arketing efforts. In the concall, the CEO (who took over w.e.f. Feb=9226) h=
ighlighted the focus on building an agile salesforce and a product suite th=
at can deliver across market cycles to ultimately deliver =93growth=94. We =
believe we should look out in this quarter for the structural rejuvenation =
of India=92s oldest AMC under new leadership and a vibrant team. We raise o=
ur TP slightly to INR 1,100 (from INR 1,050 earlier), valuing the AMC at 14=
x FY27E EPS of INR 78 (against 13x FY28E EPS of INR 82 earlier). We maintai=
n ADD.



Indian Energy Exchange | 4QFY26 first cut: In-line; coupling overhang conti=
nues<https://jmflresearch.com/Download?ReportId=3D21216&DownloadType=3Dshow=
>

Flash Update

IEX reported in-line results, with trading volumes growing 24% YoY. FY26 ma=
rket clearing prices in the DAM (-14% YoY) and RTM (-16% YoY) declined due =
to subdued power demand and increase in supply side liquidity. Key highligh=
ts from the 4QFY26 results are as follows- Revenue increased 23% YoY to INR=
 1.7 bn (-3% vs. JMFe / +3% consensus), driven by 24% YoY growth in trading=
 volumes.- EBITDA margin reported at 85.7% vs. 85.3% / 86.1% in 4QFY25 / JM=
Fe.- PAT came at INR 1.3 bn (11% YoY / -9% JMFe / -4% Cons), due to lower t=
han expected other income (-32% YoY / -41% JMFe).- Market clearing prices i=
n the DAM (Day-Ahead Market) and RTM (Real-Time Market) stood at INR 3.86 p=
er unit and INR 3.59 per unit, down 14% and 16% YoY due to increased supply=
 liquidity on the exchange.- The Board of Directors announced a final divid=
end of INR 2.0 per share.



Tips Music | Strong end to FY26; steady guidance for FY27<https://jmflresea=
rch.com/Download?ReportId=3D21214&DownloadType=3Dshow>

Result Update              ADD                 INR 730

Tips Music reported strong 4QFY26 earnings growth of 92.9% YoY, driven by 3=
2.4% revenue growth (19.1%/10.7%/21.4% in 1Q/2Q/3QFY26) and ~2,660bps EBIT =
margin expansion. Top-line growth was supported by sustained traction in th=
e company=92s catalogue, particularly its 90s repertoire, with management r=
eiterating that growth was entirely recurring with no one-offs. Paid subscr=
iption contribution has inched up to 10=9615% of digital revenue (10=9612% =
last year). Margin expansion was largely led by lower content spends (down =
54.6% YoY) due to deferment of a key movie-based music content release to 1=
QFY27. We broadly factor in management=92s revenue guidance of ~20% revenue=
 growth in FY27 (up from 15% expected earlier) but build content spends at =
the lower end of the guidance of INR 800mn-900mn basis historical under-del=
ivery. Overall, we raise FY27E=9628E EPS by 12=9615%. We roll-forward to Ma=
r=9227 TP for a revised TP of INR 730 (INR 580 earlier) as we now value the=
 stock at 32x P/E versus 30x earlier.



Bharat Electronics | Order momentum strong; valuations expensive<https://jm=
flresearch.com/Download?ReportId=3D21213&DownloadType=3Dshow>

Company Update                     ADD                 INR 485

Bharat Electronics (BEL) is well placed to benefit from rising capex in Ind=
ia=92s defence electronics. In our view, it could be a key beneficiary of e=
lectronic components, avionics and radar orders across large defence platfo=
rms. The company has secured order inflows of INR 300bn in FY26 (+60% YoY) =
ahead of its guidance of INR 270bn. We expect this ordering momentum to per=
sist in FY27 too, with strong prospects of over INR 500bn. We forecast reve=
nue/EPS CAGR of 16% each over FY26=9628E. However, BEL=92s valuation discou=
nt to capital goods growth stocks is close to an all-time low (discount at =
8% versus 10-year average of 30%). In our view, the current stock price lar=
gely reflects these positives. We value BEL at 44x FY28 EPS of INR 11, arri=
ving at our revised TP of INR 485 and assume coverage with an ADD rating.



Bharat Heavy Electricals | Journey of growth and profit begins<https://jmfl=
research.com/Download?ReportId=3D21221&DownloadType=3Dshow>

Company Update                     BUY                 INR 393

BHEL has run up 32% in just one month versus 20%/19% for S&P BSE Industrial=
s/Power index. We believe order book has not yet peaked given 18/14GW of pi=
peline along with improving non-thermal visibility. With the commissioning =
of 8.9/10GW of legacy projects, pickup in both execution and margin is cert=
ain in our view. Moreover, we reckon the permission to import from China, c=
hange in product mix in non-thermal orders (HVDC, naval guns, nuclear), ind=
igenisation of supercritical and op-lev would propel margins to mid-teens o=
ver next two=96three years. Easing of working capital stress is also likely=
 considering large customer advances and commissioning of legacy projects. =
The stock is trading at 27x FY28E EPS (consensus) at Q4FY26E EBITDA margin =
of 11% (consensus). We anticipate a beat on margins, making it worthy of an=
 earnings upgrade and re-rating as revenues compound 20% over FY25=9628E wh=
ile EBITDA margin expands from 4.4% to 11.2% in base case and RoE improves =
to at least 15% by FY28E (versus 25=9630% over 2008=9612 cycle). These fact=
ors call for a premium in our view; accordingly, we value the stock at a P/=
E of 32x (up from 30x), yielding a revised TP of INR 393 (INR 345 earlier);=
 reiterate =91BUY=92.

