<p class=3D"eqbodytext1"><span lang=3D"EN-GB" style=3D"font-size:12.0pt; fo=
nt-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif">Infosys reported 4QFY26 results =
=96 revenue and margins were below expectations. Revenue declined 1.3% cc Q=
oQ vs expectation of 0.5% cc QoQ decline. EBIT margins
 at 20.9% =96 missed JMFL and consensus expectations. Forward looking indic=
ators =96 i) Infosys guided for 1.5%-3.5% YoY cc revenue growth for FY27 (i=
ncludes 20-25bps of acquisition), lower than our expectation of 2% to 4%, m=
argin guidance was in-line at 20-22%.
 ii) LTM large deal TCV grew ~28% YoY in FY26 versus decline of ~34% in FY2=
5 (LTM book to bill of 0.74x in FY26 versus 0.60x in FY25). ii) Headcount d=
eclined 2.6% QoQ / up 1.6% YoY. iii) Management commentary =96 Lower end of=
 guidance factors demand deterioration
 while top end factors demand improvement. Margin headwinds for FY27 also i=
ncludes a potential 70bps dilutive impact from acquisitions. Prefer Infosys=
 among the top 6 Indian IT companies given healthy large deal wins. Valuati=
ons are at ~16x FY27 consensus EPS.
