 per unit and INR 3.59 per unit, down 14% and 16% YoY due to increased supp=
ly liquidity on the exchange.- The Board of Directors announced a final div=
idend of INR 2.0 per share.</span><span style=3D"font-size:12.0pt; font-fam=
ily:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif"></span></p>
