n></p>
<p class=3D"eqbodytext1"><span lang=3D"EN-GB" style=3D"font-size:12.0pt; fo=
nt-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif">Bharat Electronics (BEL) is well =
placed to benefit from rising capex in India=92s defence electronics. In ou=
r view, it could be a key beneficiary of electronic
 components, avionics and radar orders across large defence platforms. The =
company has secured order inflows of INR 300bn in FY26 (&#43;60% YoY) ahead=
 of its guidance of INR 270bn. We expect this ordering momentum to persist =
in FY27 too, with strong prospects of
 over INR 500bn. We forecast revenue/EPS CAGR of 16% each over FY26=9628E. =
However, BEL=92s valuation discount to capital goods growth stocks is close=
 to an all-time low (discount at 8% versus 10-year average of 30%). In our =
view, the current stock price largely
 reflects these positives. We value BEL at 44x FY28 EPS of INR 11, arriving=
 at our revised TP of INR 485 and assume coverage with an ADD rating.</span=
><span style=3D"font-size:12.0pt; font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-seri=
f"></span></p>
